Class OptimizerServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
        • OptimizerServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig
    @WebServlet("/optimizer")
public class OptimizerServlet
extends javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
    A Servlet class to handle post calls. This class handles the optimization and non-optimization functions like saving or uploading files.

      • getLinearElevation

        protected double getLinearElevation​(int startnode,
                                    int endnode,
                                    double length,
                                    double totallength,
                                    NodeStruct[] nodesArray)
        Calculates the linear elevation between two nodes based on the provided parameters. Get elevation of a point between startnode and endnode
        Parameters:
        startnode - The starting node ID.
        endnode - The ending node ID.
        length - The length of the segment between the two nodes.
        totallength - The total length of the path containing the segment, that is total distance between startnode and endnode
        nodesArray - An array of NodeStruct objects containing node information.
        Returns:
        The linear elevation between the start and end nodes.
